{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de8aa9fe-e2dc-4993-953c-186645038439","content":"The directory only contains the `.template.config` folder — there are no actual template source files. Here's my assessment:\n\n**Not ready to publish.** Several issues:\n\n1. **No source files** — The template has no project files (`.csproj`, `.cs`, etc.) to scaffold. A template package needs actual content.\n\n2. **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation and editor support.\n\n3. **`Framework` symbol is non-functional** — It defines a `choice` parameter but has no `replaces` property, so selecting `net8.0` or `net9.0` won't substitute into any `<TargetFramework>` element in the output.\n\n4. **Missing recommended fields for NuGet:**\n   - `groupIdentity` — needed so NuGet can group related templates.\n   - `preferNameDirectory` — typically `true` for project templates.\n   - `defaultName` — provides a fallback project name.\n\n5. **No `.nuspec` or pack-ready `.csproj`** — You'll need one to create the NuGet package itself.\n\n**Minimum to fix:** add template source files, add `replaces` to the `Framework` symbol (e.g., `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"`), add `groupIdentity`, and create a packaging project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51f889b3-9123-43c6-9f8b-08a087d34770","outputTokens":324,"requestId":"403C:1ECF:663187D:7284C3F:69EC0F9F"},"id":"903c0db4-bc27-4f9b-b5f2-df13076b8d29","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:49:44.626Z","parentId":"469e29a8-1c6b-4a16-8121-9a25333ca90d"}
